<p>Reading this, I can't help but wonder, given the form it takes: What if it only goes after people traveling above some specific speed (like 55 MPH)? Under that speed, you're perfectly safe, but the instant you go above it, by even the smallest margin, the SCP comes after you. It fits the form better, without significantly reducing the danger. After all, how many people really drive below the speed limit on a highway? Maybe even have that limit go down if conditions are less than perfect, but not by any set or predictable amount, so at most times you don't even know what the safe speed is.</p>
